items.title: Emmanuel Clase arrested at JFK, pleads not guilty in pitch rigging case
items.description: Clase and his teammate, Luis Ortiz, are both accused of being involved in a "scheme to rig bets on pitches."

items.title: WATCH:  Former ABC News senior correspondent Jim Avila dies at 69
items.description: Jim Avila, former ABC News senior correspondent and “20/20” correspondent, passed away after a long illness. He was 69 years old.

items.description: Blue Origin, owned by Jeff Bezos, plans to challenge SpaceX with the powerful, partially reusable New Glenn rocket.

items.title: Food insecurity around the U.S. has risen this year, survey finds
items.description: Roughly 14% of U.S. households reported being food insecure between January and October, up from 12.5% in 2024, Purdue University researchers found.

items.title: U.S. reaches trade frameworks with Argentina, Guatemala, El Salvador and Ecuador
items.description: The agreements will likely affect the prices of things like cocoa, bananas and coffee.

items.title: Death row inmate granted clemency right before his scheduled execution
items.description: Tremane Wood was scheduled to be executed in Oklahoma on Thursday. Gov. Kevin Sitt commuted his death sentence to life imprisonment without parole.
